{"parse":{"title":"poultry","pageid":69602,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|pultrie}}, from {{der|en|fro|pouleterie}}, from {{m|fro|poulet}}, diminutive of {{m|fr|poule||hen}}, from {{der|en|la|pullus||chick}}. {{surf|en|poult|-ry}}.\n\nFor the development of Middle English {{IPAchar|/u/}} to modern {{IPAchar|/oʊ/|/əʊ/}} before {{IPAchar|/lt/|/ld/|/ln/}}, compare {{m|en|boult}}, {{m|en|boulder}}, {{m|en|colter}}/{{m|en|coulter}}, {{m|en|poultice}}, {{m|en|shoulder}}, {{m|en|won't}}.<ref>{{R:Jespersen MEGoHP|I|10.33|290}}</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpɒltɹi/|/ˈpəʊltɹi/|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpoʊltɹi/|a=US,CA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-poultry.ogg|a=Southern California}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpɔltɹi/|/ˈpəʉltɹi/|a=AU}}\n* {{hmp|en|paltry|qq1=some accents}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|-|+}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q178559}} [[domestic|Domestic]] [[fowl]] (e.g. [[chicken]]s, [[duck]]s, [[turkey]]s, [[geese]]) raised for [[food]] ([[meat]], [[egg]]s, or both).\n#: {{hyper|en|bird<id:Q5113>|<|animal<id:Q729>|<|creature#Noun|critter#Noun}}\n#: {{hypo|en|chicken<id:Q780>|hen<id:Q2201314>|rooster|pullet<id:young hen>|chick<id:Q65167027>|;|duck|duckling|;|turkey<id:Q848706>|gobbler<id:turkey>|;|goose|gander|gosling}}\n#: {{coi|en|a '''poultry''' farmer}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q18087876}}The meat from a domestic fowl.\n#: {{hyper|en|meat<id:Q10990>|<|food<id:Q2095>}}\n#: {{hypo|en|chicken<id:Q864693>|turkey<id:Q4200953>|quail<id:Q7268510>}}\n#: {{coi|en|the '''poultry''' counter}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|nonpoultry|poultrydom|poultryhouse|poultryist|poultryless|poultrylike\n|poultry wire\n|poultryman\n|poultrywoman\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|en\n|poult\n|poulter\n|poulterer\n|pullet\n|pullulate\n}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|domestic fowl}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|دَجَاج|m}}, {{t|ar|دَوَاجِن|f-p}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|دواجن|f-p|tr=dawāgen}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|دجاج|m|tr=djāj}}\n* Armenian: {{t|hy|[[ընտանի]] [[թռչուններ]]|p}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|ҡош-ҡорт}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|сво́йская пту́шка|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|птица}}, {{t|bg|дома́шна пти́ца|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|aviram|m}}, {{t|ca|volateria|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|家禽|tr=jiāqín}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|drůbež|f}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|fjerkræ|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|pluimvee|n}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kortobirdo}}, {{t|eo|kortobirdaro}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|siipikarja}}\n* French: {{qualifier|collective}} {{t+|fr|volaille|f}}, {{t+|fr|volailles|f-p}}, {{t+|fr|basse-cour|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Geflügel|n}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πουλερικά|n-p}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|baromfi}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|unggas}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|éanlaith|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|pollame|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|家禽|tr=かきん, kakin}}; {{qualifier|category or group}} {{t+|ja|家禽類|tr=かきんるい, kakin-rui}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|가금(家禽)}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|живина|f}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|[[unggas]] [[domestik]]}}, {{t|ms|poltri}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|volaille|f}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|fjærfe|n}}, {{t|nb|fjørfe|n}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|fjørfe|n}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|дробизґ|m}}, {{t|rsk|живина|f}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|ماکیان|tr=mâkiyân}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|drób|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|[[ave]] [[doméstica]]|f}}, {{t|pt|ave de capoeira|f}}, {{t|pt|[[ave]] [[de corte]]|f}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|[[домашний|дома́шняя]] [[пти́ца]]|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|живина|f}}, {{t|sh|перад|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|živina|f}}, {{t+|sh|perad|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|hydina|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|perutnina|f}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|pjerina|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|ave de corral|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|fjäderfä|n}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|kümes hayvanları|p}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|сві́йський птах|m}}, {{t|uk|сві́йська пти́ця|f}}\n* Volapük: {{qualifier|collective}} {{t+|vo|bödem}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|poytreye|f}}, {{t+|wa|poyes|f-p}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|fowl meat}}\n* Arabic:\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|دجاج|m|tr=djāj}}\